The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Aug. 14: Sebi and the Reserve Bank of India will meet soon to sort out differences over permitting institutional investors to short-sell their securities. While Sebi wants to permit all institutional investors, the RBI favours a phased approach to allow only domestic institutional investors initially. The issue of allowing institutional investors to short-sell is linked to the programme for stock lending and borrowing.

 Calcutta, Aug. 14: Allahabad Bank will revise its deposit rates between 25 basis points to 75 basis points for deposits with maturity above 180 days. The new interest rates for deposit above 181 days and less than one year is 6.25 per cent, while for maturity between two and three years the new rate is 7.25 per cent. 

 New Delhi, Aug. 14: The Prime Ministers economic advisory council has forecast that the wholesale prices-based inflation rate will be contained around 5.5 per cent at the end of this fiscal compared with 4.1 per cent last year, even if petro prices are revised again later this year.

 Mumbai, Aug. 14: Siemenss plans to acquire a 20 per cent stake in Bayer Diagnostics India Ltd have been delayed and a revised open offer schedule will be announced later.




